First, a few pre-requisites. Since you mentioned you&#39;re using a private repository, you&#39;ll need to have at least GitLab Silver (hosted on gitlab.com) or GitLab Premium (self-hosted) in order to use the [GitLab Maven Packages repository](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/project/packages/maven.html). Also, if you&#39;re self-hosted, you&#39;ll need to be on [GitLab 11.3](https://about.gitlab.com/2018/09/22/gitlab-11-3-released/) or later (should be out this time next week), and have `packages_enabled` set to true (see [Enabling the Packages repository](https://bag.org.tr/proje/help/administration/packages.md#enabling-the-packages-feature)).

For private projects, you&#39;ll need a [Personal Access Token](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/profile/personal_access_tokens.html). The token should have the `api` scope for Maven to upload artifacts to GitLab. Once you have the token, you configure your `settings.xml` like this.

    &lt;settings&gt;
      &lt;servers&gt;
        &lt;server&gt;
          &lt;id&gt;gitlab-maven&lt;/id&gt;
          &lt;configuration&gt;
            &lt;httpHeaders&gt;
              &lt;property&gt;
                &lt;name&gt;Private-Token&lt;/name&gt;
                &lt;value&gt;REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/value&gt;
              &lt;/property&gt;
            &lt;/httpHeaders&gt;
          &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/server&gt;
      &lt;/servers&gt;
    &lt;/settings&gt;

In `pom.xml`, where you have the ellipses, you need to fill in your project ID. To find the ID, just visit the front page of your project on GitLab. It&#39;s shown near the top of the pages, just after the name and description of your project. For example, take a look at the [mvn-example](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/examples/mvn-example) sample project. Its project ID is 8377576. That goes in the URL. 

    &lt;repositories&gt;
      &lt;repository&gt;
        &lt;id&gt;gitlab-maven&lt;/id&gt;
        &lt;url&gt;https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/8377576/packages/maven&lt;/url&gt;
      &lt;/repository&gt;
    &lt;/repositories&gt;

The [mvn-example project&#39;s pom.xml file](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/examples/mvn-example/blob/master/pom.xml) shows a completed example.

With all that set up, you should be able to upload artifacts with `mvn deploy`.

First of all you should go to your projects &quot;Packages and Registries&quot; it is on the left menu of your Gitlab user interface and find there package registry button(if you can&#39;t see it just ask your system administrator) and just leave that tab open and wait for future instructions.
